-- Chinese bank BoCom plans 10.8 pct loan growth this year, same as 2013
-- By Zhao Hongmei
-- Sun Mar 30, 2014 09:52PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG/SHANGHAI, March 31 (Reuters) - Bank of Communications Co Ltd <3328.HK><601328.SS> plans to increase loans by 10.8 percent in 2014, maintaining the same growth rate as in 2013, the bank's president, Peng Chun, said at a press conference on Monday.

The country's fifth largest bank posted a 2 percent drop in on-year net profit growth for the fourth quarter on Sunday, the only one of the country's top five banks to miss market forecasts. [ID:nL3N0ME1SG]